benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/emails/{email} - Delete email from account

covered: Valid Deletion scenarios (204) across multiple test cases including with/without optional headers (TC01, TC02, TC12, TC13, TC14, TC15, TC17, TC18)
Non-Existent Resource handling (404) for non-existent account, non-existent email, and no emails (TC03, TC04, TC09)
Authorization/Header validation (401 for invalid token; 400 for missing required header)
Input Validation (400 for invalid accountId, invalid email, and XSS/injection in email parameter)
Resilience/Recovery testing (transient network failure recovery in TC19)
Performance consideration (response time under 500ms in TC14)
Edge cases (very long email and minimal-length email in TC12 and TC13)
Regression scenarios (uppercase email in TC17; backward compatibility in TC18)
Concurrency coverage (multiple concurrent deletes in TC15)
Header usage variations (CreatedBy header in multiple scenarios including TC01/TC02)
gaps: Rate limiting/throttling scenarios (429 Too Many Requests) are not tested
Caching behavior testing (ETag/Cache-Control headers on DELETE) is not covered
Soft delete semantics vs hard delete is not explicitly tested
403 Forbidden scenarios (insufficient permissions) are not tested
Extensive load/concurrency stress beyond 5 concurrent requests is not covered
recommendations: Add rate limiting tests to verify proper 429 responses under high request volume
Add tests asserting caching headers and behavior for DELETE responses (ETag/Cache-Control) if applicable
Introduce a soft-delete vs hard-delete semantics test to clarify deletion behavior
Add a 403 Forbidden scenario to cover insufficient-permission cases
Introduce additional concurrency/load tests beyond TC15 to explore race conditions and stability under stress
Add tests validating end-to-end observability/logging behavior for delete operations
